set.explicate: verb: to make plain or clear, explain; to interpret
set.implicate: verb: to involve in; to connect with or be related to
set.introspective: adjective: contemplating one's own thoughts and feelings
set.perspicuity: adjective: clearness or lucidity, as of a statement
set.specious: adjective: deceptive, apparently good or valid but lacking real merit
set.speculate: verb: form a theory about a subject without firm evidence
set.actuate: verb: to move to action; to impel
set.beset: verb: (of a problem) trouble or threaten persistently.
set.dire: adjective: (of a situation or event) extremely serious or urgent
set.fervent: adjective: having or displaying a passionate intensity
set.fester: verb: to grow embittered over time; to rot
set.zealous: adjective: enthusiastic, marked by passionate support for a person, cause, or ideal
